The paper discusses decentralized resource allocation in autonomic computing systems, which involves decision-making and optimization. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of cooperative negotiation implies that the paper could also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The autonomic computing systems mentioned in the paper are self-managing, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses computational experiments, which suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
